{"lemma":"نَفْطٌ","slug":"نَفْطٌ","root":"ن.ف.ط","root_slug":"ن-ف-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ف-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40312"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"oil, petroleum, naphtha","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"turpentine","tags":["dated","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a flammable mix used in war such as Greek fire","tags":["countable","obsolete","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a kind of cannon that projects such substance, lombard","tags":["countable","obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"blisters, blebs, pustules","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"matchsticks","tags":["collective","obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic נִיפְטָא (nip̄ṭā) / נַפְטָא (nap̄ṭā) / ܢܷܦܛܳܐ (nep̄ṭā) / ܢܱܦܛܳܐ (nap̄ṭā), from Akkadian 𒉌𒆳𒊏 (napṭu, “naphtha”)."},"ipa":["/naftˤ/","/niftˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40312","headword_ar":"نَفْطٌ","root":"nfT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the T,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pustules which come forth upon the hand, in consequence of work, full of water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fluid;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blisters,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vesicles, upon the hand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a contraction of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafiTN","text_ar":"نَفِطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which is pl. [or rather coll. gen. n.] of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafiTapN","text_ar":"نَفِطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", sometimes contracted into ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafoTapN","text_ar":"نَفْطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafiTaAtN","text_ar":"نَفِطَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafiTapN","text_ar":"نَفِطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafiTapN","text_ar":"نَفِطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pustule;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafoTapN","text_ar":"نَفْطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nifoTapN","text_ar":"نِفْطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and the lawyers call it ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naf~aATapN","text_ar":"نَفَّاطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", from this word as signifying “ a place whence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nifoT","text_ar":"نِفْط"},{"kind":"text","text":"issues, ” or it may be [originally] an intensive act. part. n. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafiTN","text_ar":"نَفِطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafiTapN","text_ar":"نَفِطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafoTapN","text_ar":"نَفْطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nifoTapN","text_ar":"نِفْطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Sgh, K,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small-pox:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Sgh, Msb, K:) accord. to Z, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nfZ","text_ar":"نفظ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the TA, without any syll. signs,] signifies, in the dial. of Hudheyl, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small-pox in children"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  See also what next follows."}],"source_refs":["Msb","Mgh","Sgh","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}